    <div class="answer">
        <p>Our heart disease diagnosis system uses a variety of symptoms to help predict the likelihood of heart disease. Some of the most common symptoms include:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Chest Pain:</strong> A common symptom, often associated with a heart attack.</li>
            <li><strong>Shortness of Breath:</strong> Difficulty breathing or feeling winded can indicate heart issues.</li>
            <li><strong>Fatigue:</strong> Unusual tiredness, especially after minimal physical activity, could be a sign of heart disease.</li>
            <li><strong>Dizziness or Lightheadedness:</strong> Can occur when the heart is not pumping blood effectively.</li>
            <li><strong>Swelling in the Legs or Feet:</strong> This can indicate that the heart is struggling to pump blood properly.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>If you experience any of these symptoms, please contact a healthcare professional immediately.</p>
